\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. S. orientalis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 900 (1753). Up to 120(-190) cm pubescent. Leaves triangular-hastate, acute at apex, cuneate at base, irregularly dentate or lobed, the petiole tapering from above and more or less unwinged in its lower part, not amplexicaul. Capitula 6-9 mm across (excluding outer involucral bracts) outer involucral bracts 7-15 mm, linear-spathulate; stalked glands present on outer and inner involucral bracts and often on peduncle. 2n = 60.{\i  Naturalized in waste places and by railways in S. Romania; casual elsewhere}. [?It Rm.] ({\i Warm temperate and tropical regions of the Old World.})
